  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims on the combinatorial results of cytology, histopathology and microbiology
      obatined by EBUS-TBNA for unselected mediastina lesions.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      A number of studies have proved EBUS-TBNA to be useful for lymph node staging in lung cancer.
      The diagnostic performance is equivalent to mediastinoscopy while the invasiveness is far
      less. This study primarily focusing on merged approach of cytology, histopathology and
      microbioloogy obatined by EBUS-TBNA for unselected mediastina lesions.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
